{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51851c0c-9e41-4609-a5f0-3cd34008432b","content":"In MSTest v4, `[ExpectedException]` was **removed**. The replacement is `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` — wrap the throwing call inside it:\n\n```csharp\n// Before (v3):\n[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()\n{\n    Validate(null);\n}\n\n// After (v4):\n[TestMethod]\npublic void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()\n{\n    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));\n}\n```\n\nThis is better because:\n- The assertion is **scoped** to the exact line you expect to throw, not the entire method body.\n- You get back the exception instance to assert on its `Message`, `ParamName`, etc.\n- For `async` methods, use `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()`.\n\nWant me to apply these fixes to your file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b533f32b-682a-4b1c-9fc4-35cf4490af61","outputTokens":248,"requestId":"A040:22220D:1C374E6:2054A2E:69FEA284"},"id":"df67efe4-1cd0-47f8-acd6-4bbaf9a27601","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:57:14.596Z","parentId":"0450da39-035e-48f4-b3be-25e4e96e38f2"}
